    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sheet metal seams formed by slipping a cap strip, which is a narrow metal strip that has had long edges turned, over the turned edges of the two metal pieces to be joined, to form a lock. An example of use is in assembling cross seams of ducts.</Note_Text>
